Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

While it boils, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{480%grams} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's
> cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use
a #garlic press{}).

Zest and halve the @Lime{1/2}(zested and halved).

Once the water has boiled, pour into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high
heat.

Add the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back into the #pot{}. Cover with a #lid{} and
leave to the side until ready to serve.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir in the garlic, @Ginger Puree{15%grams} and
@Tomato Puree{30%grams}. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @Coconut Milk{180%milliliters}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams},
@Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{50%milliliters} for the sauce, then stir together.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir the @Peas{120%grams} into the stew.

Remove from the heat, squeeze in some lime juice and stir in the @Soy Sauce{15%milliliters}.

Taste and add more lime juice if needed. Add a splash more water if it's a bit too thick.

Share the rice between your bowls and spoon the chicken stew on top.

Finish with a sprinkling of lime zest. Enjoy!